MIME media type name : Application

MIME subtype name : Vendor Tree - vnd.spotfire.dxp

Required parameters : none

Optional parameters :
none

Encoding considerations : binary
This media type may require encoding on transports not capable of handling binary.

Security considerations :
Documents of the MIME-type contain data and references to functions (code). These 
functions and code can only be run within the application and only run functions 
available from within the application. It is therefore not possible to execute any ordinary 
command-line or operating system functions from the files of the specified MIME-type. 
All settings and configuration files associated with the product have checksums and all 
sensitive information is encrypted. All executable files in the product are digitally signed.

Interoperability considerations :
None known

Published specification :
Specification by example:
By using the TIBCO Spotfire product available from TIBCO Software Inc.
(http://spotfire.tibco.com) start the application and select File>Save As, input a file name 
and click the Ok button. You have now created a file type that corresponds to this MIME 
Content-Type.


Applications which use this media :
TIBCO Spotfire

Additional information :

1. Magic number(s) : None
2. File extension(s) : dxp
3. Macintosh file type code : None
4. Object Identifiers: None
